          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "سَأَلَ أَبُو اَلْجَارُودِ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ:"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " عَنِ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "اَلرَّجُلِ يُتَوَفَّى أَ تُقَلَّمُ أَظَافِيرُهُ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "يُنْتَفُ إِبْطَاهُ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "تُحْلَقُ عَانَتُهُ إِنْ طَالَتْ بِهِ مِنَ اَلْمَرَضِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " فَقَالَ"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:25:20",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/25/418",
      "text": [
        " «لاَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.418 - Abu al-Jaroud asked Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) about a man who passed away: Should his nails be trimmed, his armpit hair plucked, or his pubic hair shaved if he had been bedridden for a long period?\nImam (as) said: \"No.\""
        ]
      }
    },
